An explosion in Kabba, Kogi State, has thrown residents into confusion. The incident was said to have occurred opposite Mannajot Petrol Station on Sunday evening, with a yet-to-be-ascertained number of people feared injured. SaharaReporters Media Details of the blast are still sketchy but a security source linked the bomb explosion to the Islamic State-backed faction of Boko Haram, the Islamic State West Africa Province (ISWAP), formerly known as Jamā'at Ahl as-Sunnah lid-Da'wah wa'l-Jihād. ISWAP had in April claimed responsibility for an attack on a police station in Adavi Local Government Area of the state. See Also







